    {
      "id": "ee07697b6563120a3adb77f4483c8bece4b57a0c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-12 16:55:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nBetter to define an ll_umode_t macro that maps to the correct argument type for the kernel. That way for upstream submission it is easy to use sed to replace ll_umode_t -> umode_t in the code, instead of having to edit several places in the code.\n\nAlso, it would be better if the 3.3 patches were before the 3.4 patches in the series so that they can land first and we at least get 3.3 working instead of half of each kernel. Ideally, each patch would be submitted independently, but they all conflict in the lustre-core.m4 file. It should at least be possible to have a separate 3.3 stream and a 3.4 stream of patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
